Required:

1-The MAX-HEAPIFY procedure: is the key to maintaining the max-heap property and runs in O (lg n) time.

parameter:an element index in an array and the array ?
output: the element shifted in its place in the array to make it a maximum heap? (without affecting the original heap

2-The BUILD-MAX-HEAP procedure produces a max-heap from an unordered input array and runs in O(n)

parameter: an array of unordered integers (or values)
o/p: it should make a maximum heap out of it (an array ordered as a maximum heap)

3-The HEAPSORT procedure: sorts an array in place and which runs in O (n lg n) time


